# GCP Vertex AI

Primary metrics from GCP Vertex AI service. This dashboard contains: 

- Invocation rates
- Error rates
- Token usage
- Model Invocation latency
- Prediction metrics
- Resource Utilization

embeddableConfig.description: Total number of model invocations (prediction requests).
Top 10 model usage group-by the resource id of the PublisherModel.
Total error response code of prediction request.
Count of input and output tokens usage over the period group-by top 3 models.
Total errors over the period group-by top 3 error response codes.

panelsJSON.title: Overall error rate - by response code

embeddableConfig.description: Count of invocations over the period group-by top 5 model usage.
Invocation latency over the period in milliseconds group-by top 5 model usage.
Consumed throughput count over the period group-by top 5 model usage.
Number of online predictions over the period group-by endpoint.
Online prediction latency in milliseconds over the period group-by endpoint.
Number of online prediction errors over the period group-by endpoint.

Fraction of CPU allocated by the deployed model replica and currently in use. May exceed 100% if the machine type has multiple CPUs. Sampled every 60 seconds. After sampling data is not visible for up to 360 seconds.
Amount of memory allocated by the deployed model replica and currently in use. Sampled every 60 seconds. After sampling data is not visible for up to 360 seconds.
Number of bytes sent and received over the network by the deployed model replica. Sampled every 60 seconds. After sampling data is not visible for up to 360 seconds.
